The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as object detection and instance segmentation, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel deep architecture for these tasks, which involves learning features jointly on both the object level and the pixel level, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also involves extensive experimental analyses and comparisons, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper deals with image and video processing (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) as it involves object detection and segmentation, which are important tasks in these fields.
